The <a href="glossary.html#api" title="Application Programming Interface" class="glossary-term">API</a> is great. We also use <a href="glossary.html#rest" title="Representational State Transfer." class="glossary-term">REST</a> for transport.

````rust
let api = ApiClient::new();
````

Inline `API` should not link. Visit [the API docs](docs.html).

 > [!NOTE]
 > The API handles auth, while <a href="glossary.html#xpt" class="glossary-term">XPT</a> is a legacy format.
